Subject: [PATCH] SwiftCompiler: never statically link the Swift stdlib into
 host macro-plugin products

`--static-swift-stdlib` sets `SWIFT_FORCE_STATIC_LINK_STDLIB` globally, and
`staticallyLinkSwiftStdlib` honored it for *every* product, including macro
implementation plugins. A macro plugin is dlopen'd by `swift-plugin-server`
(which already links the Swift runtime dynamically); statically linking the
stdlib into the plugin embeds a second runtime, which conflicts at load time
and makes the plugin fail to vend its macros:

  error: external macro implementation type 'X.Y' could not be found for
  macro '...'; '.../Plugin' produced malformed response

This blocks any macro-using package (e.g. swift-java's `@JavaClass`) from
cross-compiling under `--static-swift-stdlib`, even though the target product
links fine statically. Gate on `SWIFT_IMPLEMENTS_MACROS_FOR_MODULE_NAMES`
(set on macro-implementation products) and always link those plugins
dynamically; target products still honor the static flag.
---
diff --git a/Sources/SWBCore/SpecImplementations/Tools/SwiftCompiler.swift b/Sources/SWBCore/SpecImplementations/Tools/SwiftCompiler.swift
index 84f271ff..c10be633 100644
--- a/Sources/SWBCore/SpecImplementations/Tools/SwiftCompiler.swift
+++ b/Sources/SWBCore/SpecImplementations/Tools/SwiftCompiler.swift
@@ -2594,6 +2594,20 @@ public final class SwiftCompilerSpec : CompilerSpec, SpecIdentifierType, SwiftDi
         //
         // NOTE: With Swift in the OS, static libs aren't being supplied by the toolchains
         //       so users of this flag will need to provide their own.
+
+        // A product that implements macros is a compiler plugin: it is dlopen'd
+        // by swift-plugin-server, which already has its own dynamically-linked
+        // Swift runtime. Statically linking the stdlib into the plugin embeds a
+        // second copy of the runtime, which conflicts at load time and makes the
+        // plugin fail to vend its macro implementations ("external macro
+        // implementation type '...' could not be found ... produced malformed
+        // response"). Always link such host plugins dynamically, even when
+        // --static-swift-stdlib (SWIFT_FORCE_STATIC_LINK_STDLIB) is requested for
+        // the build's target products.
+        if !scope.evaluate(BuiltinMacros.SWIFT_IMPLEMENTS_MACROS_FOR_MODULE_NAMES, lookup: lookup).isEmpty {
+            return false
+        }
+
         if scope.evaluate(BuiltinMacros.SWIFT_FORCE_STATIC_LINK_STDLIB, lookup: lookup) {
             return true
         }
